The initial laying out of creditentials may result in what appears to be chest beating.  It could be an attempt to vent anger about the suffering, the loss of close friends.. etc.  Perhaps it is the residuals of an intense indoctrination of  pride and obligation that young Marines receive in order that they might be able to meet the greatest test.  Some are unable to meet the standards in training.  Some are unwilling to try.  Only a few make it onto the battlefield, fewer make it off.<br>
I would venture to say that two minutes in a fire fight is a greater contribution to freedom than two years of pushing bedpans.<br>
Many servicemen did more than one tour in Viet Nam because some of the REMF's had it pretty good (SOME DID'NT).  Combat veterans, served more that one tour usually because they held a critical MOS (military occupation speciality) or they had unfinished business to take care of (hatred.. remorse.. etc.)<br>
Bro. Cookie... one tour is enough!  One outstanding tour is more than enough!!  WELCOME HOME JARHEAD!<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
